Police in Jigawa State has confirmed the death of 36 persons in different motor accidents in the state. This was contained in a statement signed by the spokesman of the Jigawa State Police Command, ASP Lawan Shiisu Adam, issued to DAILY POST. He said the deaths were recorded in 21 different accidents which occurred in the month of February, 2022. DAILY POST reported that nine persons last week lost their lives in an accident that involved a Volkswagen Golf three and a tricycle in Birniwa Local Government Area of the state. Shiisu explained that those that lost their lives include men, women and children as well as properties worth millions of Naira were lost. “During the period the command had also recorded 52 cases including; rape, five armed robberies, nine culpable homicide and 21 accidents,” he said. The command, therefore, warned drivers to be extra careful and avoid overloading and dangerous overtaking.